100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 5, 1925, the League of Nations met in Geneva to address growing tensions in Europe, particularly concerning the ongoing disputes between Greece and Bulgaria. In the United States, the trial of John Scopes, accused of teaching evolution in Tennessee, continued to draw national attention, highlighting the clash between science and religion. Meanwhile, in India, Mahatma Gandhi was released from prison, further energizing the independence movement against British rule.
